Target: OntoIsochrone is an ontology for describing isochrones.

Comment: Polygon describing the area reachable within a stipulated time threshold.
Label: Isochrone

Comment: A relationship between an isochrone and the entities where its originated from.
Label: originates from

Comment: Transport mode refers to the way people are transported.
Label: Transport Mode

Comment: Drive refers to the act of travelling via a motorized vehicle.
Label: Drive

Comment: Cycle refers to the act of travelling via a bicycle.
Label: Cycle

Comment: Walk refers to the act of traveling on foot.
Label: Walk

Comment: Road conditions describes the conditions of the road.
Label: Road Conditions

Comment: A relationship between an isochrone and its time threshold.
Label: has time threshold

Comment: A relationship between an isochrone and its covered total population number.
Label: has total population

Comment: A relationship between an isochrone and its covered men population number.
Label: has men population

Comment: A relationship between an isochrone and its covered women population number.
Label: has women population

Comment: A relationship between an isochrone and its covered women of reproductive age (age 15 - 49) population number.
Label: has women of reproductive age population

Comment: A relationship between an isochrone and its covered children (age under 5) population number.
Label: has children population

Comment: A relationship between an isochrone and its covered youth (age 15 - 24) population number.
Label: has youth population

Comment: A relationship between an isochrone and its covered elderly (age above 60) population number.
Label: has elderly population
